\frac{1}{2} \int_0^1 (u_t^2(x, t) + u_x^2(x, t))dx
E
 K(t)=\frac 12\int_0^1 u_{t}^2dx. 
 \frac{dK}{dt}(t)=\int_0^1u_tu_{tt}dx=\text{(due to the equation)}=\int_0^1u_tu_{xx} dx. 
 \int_0^1u_tu_{xx}dx=u_tu_{x}|_0^1-\int_0^1 u_{x}u_{xt}dx=-\frac 12\frac{d}{dt}\int_0^1u_x^2\,dx=:-\frac{dT}{dt}(t).  
 \frac{dK}{dt}(t)=-\frac{dT}{dt}(t)\implies K(t)+T(t)=E, 
